===Glyph origin===
{{Han etyl}}
{{liushu|i}} – From {{zh-l|*口}} and ▽(possibly original form of {{zh-l|*弋}}, marking location). Later: from {{zh-l|*口}} and {{zh-l|*辛}} or {{zh-l|*䇂}} (possibly mixed with {{zh-l|*舌}}).

Possibly related to the semantic family of {{zh-l|*舌}} ("protruding/emerging", opposite to {{zh-l|*音}} "converging/covering") or {{zh-l|*語}} ("facing/front"). May also relate to {{zh-l|*獻}}, {{zh-l|*諺}}, and {{zh-l|*唁}} ("formal presentation/declaration").

See also {{zh-l|*音}}.

===Etymology 1===
According to {{zh-ref|Schuessler (2007: 74)}} this word is derived from {{och-l|語|id=1|to speak}} + ''-n'' nominal suffix.

